02 10:40:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=538.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /rude guild.</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;a level 51 has just as much right to be there as the level 10s&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
To me, the level of the characters is not the issue.  Both parties had a right to the camp.  Neither party had an exclusive right to dominate the camp for four hours.<br>
<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;If there are newbies around, I just toss my spiffy little damage shield on them instead&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
Stunning the mob works well, too.  No damage, so you can't steal credit for the kill, it stobs the mob from attacking or running temporarily, so it helps the newbie, and you'll both get the faction hit.  Or you can wait until the mob is well below half health and kill it, but I prefer Stun, as it is so much less likely to worry the newbie that maybe you are trying to kill-steal.  When I played a monk, I would throw a single shuriken at the mob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 538<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/14/02 11:00:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=538.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /rude guild.</span><hr size=1> I am neutral on this account too few details.  In general I would expect a 51 to not tie up Orc camps forever, but at the same time if you want to use the RP aspect of the server, it could be valid RP for him to do so.  &quot;Play nice Policy&quot; while useful, is an entirely OOC set of rules - necessary mind you, but OOC.<br>
<br>
As to the Deathfist Belts and Faction - you can turn them in in two places.  Give them to the Militia and get +Militia -KnightsOfTruth, give them to the Knights and get the opposite. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/14/02 11:23:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=538.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   well...</span><hr size=1> First the belts aren't affected by TLC.<br>
<br>
Second there are two different quests you can do with those belts to repair faction. One lowers the guard faction the other raises it. You can do both in wolf form and not be KoS (is you are already KoS).<br>
<br>
Third, I have no idea why this high level person would be such an ass, but I wouldnt dismiss the whole server just because of this one person.<br>
<br>
Verant has no way of enforcing the &quot;role play&quot; part of the FV server. Its simply a suggestion. Many people play on this server for alot of different reasons despite what Verant may have wanted the server to be used for.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is no matter where you are you will run into people you dont agree with. The only thing that matters is how you decide to behave here... and hopefully that will eventually result in your being happy here.<br>
