Actually this is pretty sillly on the whole. Have at thee orc ! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukneczhevo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kneczhevo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/15/02 5:34:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=538.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Clarification</span><hr size=1> First of all, I am suprised that no names were mentioned (good and/or bad).<br>
<br>
Secondly...  I will say I have been one of the offenders of this so called &quot;Farming&quot; of the orc camps in the past, but not to this situation.<br>
<br>
My story is...  I am an Iksar Shaman.  Being one of &quot;evil&quot; lieniage, I have few places to rest my weary bones on those long treks from my homeland, Cabilis.  So, one of the simple solutions is to become friendly with the residence of Freeport.  Also, part of epic quest involves traveling in this ilgotten place of the softskins.<br>
<br>
Personally, I just sit and slaughter the camp..  preferably the one to the west in West Commons.  No need for me to loot the carcasses..  I have no place to bank and the copper was/isn't worth my trouble to get off my arse and risk loosing my camp.  Besides, I figure the youngens could use the pennies to upgrade thier attire, and they can have all the belts to thier hearts content.<br>
<br>
Now then, I have come across quite a few youngens who were grateful at my scraps and were curious as to my doings.  Great conversations and I educated them in the why's &quot;a bear&quot; is slaugtering orcs, besides despising those orcs for ruining the softskins lands.  Some have asked if they could steal some of the perpitrators, I always reply, &quot;if you can snag one from my pet, you are more than welcome&quot; (I have a 1st level, 5pt nuke, for faction tag and buffs/heals work too.)  But the latter is so time consuming (PLing), when my pet can slaughter the camp in minutes and I have been here a week already (weigh those factors).<br>
<br>
Then again, I have run into those select few that would attempt to &quot;evict me&quot;.  If they come up to me and say, &quot; Exuse me, all the other camps are taken, may my group have this camp?&quot;  I would comply and sit on the sidelines.  Now, if they come up and say, &quot;Dood!  Your farming!  Get out!&quot;  Guess what?  And this has happened.<br>
<br>
This reminds me of the time I was doing my fourth shawl in EW, on a blue server...  When I was trying to trigger Tanik.  I had to zone from the Death Squads.  When I came back a druid had taken the middle of the ramp and claimed that he had the Tanik Camp and that I had no right to it.  I obviously saw he did not know what he was doing (because the spoiler gives wrong info).  So, I continued about my bussiness.  But, because he had a mob charmed, my pet kept looking at his pet.  Well, he got irate after I pulled a DS in his general direction after /shouting knowing he was threre (yes, I am still curtious, even to jerks).  He then goes off on those colorful discriptions about my lieniage and other forms of name calling.  Well, when his frustrations got the best of him and he decided to leave, guess who spawned?  Takes about nine DSes, FYI.  I have done that darned quest so many times now &lt;frown&gt;.<br>
<br>
Moral of the story...<br>
<br>
We did not design the game and we are not exploting any rules (faction farming).  If you feel the need to talk to someone about thier behaviour, talk to them, don't threaten nore become irrate.  I have as much time playing as you do, folks.<br>
<br>
