Enchantress of the Jeweled Rose</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/02 4:43:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=538.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The only thing he could have wanted ..</span><hr size=1> .. was faction and perhaps belts.  However, orcs are about one of the slowest ways to fix faction with FP.  Smart faction fixers use Tumpy Tonics or (a bit slower) buy scalps from newbies in HPH.  Starting from scowly with a full pack of 160 tonics, Mo became non-KoS over all of FP and still has over 100 tonics in the bank.  Total time for this faction work?  About 2H.  Only an idiot farms belts for FP faction.<br>
<br>
On the camp issue, I feel like most, though.  Level doesn't matter.  If he's keeping the spawn down, the camp is his.  He owns it for as long as he cares to keep spawn down.  Whether or not it's worth owning is a separate issue.  PnP only applies to GMs.  PnP is the only viable way for GMs to settle disputes.  It's not what most players use.  <br>
<br>
